1
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,680
Let's go get changed, so we can go.

2
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:01,000
I'm getting tired.

3
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:11,240
It made me see clearly

4
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:14,360
where I really belong.

5
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:22,120
Because my son's made the same mistake.

6
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:29,760
That's why I'm worried about Mr. Thee,
since I'm a mother like you.

7
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:36,680
If you can't make Ms. Mook happy,
then you should let her go.

8
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:39,680
This is my problem.

9
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:41,160
I can deal with it myself.

10
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:46,400
Mook.

11
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:52,600
Here are the photos reshot yesterday
for you to choose from.

12
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:56,240
You know, you don't have to do this, Mook.

13
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,160
- I'll go talk to my--
- It's not an issue for us.

14
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:02,840
We're happy to edit our work
as our clients see fit.

15
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:06,240
If you really want to help,

16
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:11,040
please choose the photos
and finalize this project.

17
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,200
No! Wait, Mr.--

18
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:17,280
Why'd you remove Ms. Narin
from her position?

19
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:19,600
How could you do this?

20
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:23,920
I'm a co-investor,
and I'm the hotel's majority shareholder.

21
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:27,280
I have the authority to replace the board.

22
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,240
It's perfectly normal.

23
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:35,760
I might even consider
more ways of restructuring soon.

24
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:39,840
But when we made the deal,
you never mentioned this.

25
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,840
Well, this is what I want to do now.

26
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:44,800
Do you have a problem with that?

27
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,080
I don't.

28
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:54,040
I'm just thinking of a way
to tell Ms. Narin.

29
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,440
Don't worry about it.

30
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,840
I'll handle it myself.

31
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,080
Got it, Mr. Thee.

32
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,800
Why'd you remove Ms. Narin?

33
00:04:17,760 --> 00:04:19,680
Or did you buy up all the shares to…

34
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,880
Let's go over our work.

35
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,640
Is Boss not here, Mr. Suetrong?

36
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:57,560
Oh, he left this afternoon.

37
00:04:57,640 --> 00:05:00,240
I heard he had to take care of something,
and he won't be back.

38
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,560
Is it urgent?

39
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,600
I have to talk to him about work.

40
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:04,520
I'll just do it later.

41
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:13,120
- A little to the left.
- Left?

42
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,480
Left, please.

43
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:16,160
- Is that good?
- A little more.

44
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:18,400
Wait. A little to the right.

45
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:20,800
To the right, and up a bit.

46
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,000
Okay.

47
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,680
- Is that good?
- Yes.

48
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:35,440
Here, I'll help.

49
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,320
Thanks.

50
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:40,960
- Make sure it's straight.
- Good?

51
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:41,880
Yes.

52
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:54,440
This is my husband's old house.

53
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:57,080
I'll use this place
for storing campaign materials

54
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:58,960
and to hold meetings with the staff,

55
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:02,080
so we won't have to bother
using our party's office.

56
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,760
Sounds like a good idea, Prao.

57
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:07,880
Let's go.

58
00:06:17,360 --> 00:06:18,480
This is Pat's car.

59
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:32,240
Does it match?

60
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,880
Did I arrange them right?

61
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:37,080
Hey, your face got dirty.

62
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:41,680
Hold on. You're making it worse.

63
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:42,920
Let me get it for you.

64
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:46,880
It's all over your face.

65
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:05,840
Pat!

66
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,320
Prao.

67
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,360
I just caught you red-handed.

68
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,520
Still got any excuses?

69
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:17,440
Caught what?

70
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:24,960
Well, I caught you and Pat
messing around here, of course!

71
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:28,120
Then, you've misunderstood us.

72
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:30,320
We haven't even gone that far yet.

73
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:33,200
Please show a little respect.

74
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,440
You want respect?

75
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:40,080
Then you shouldn't have been so obnoxious!

76
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:45,760
You're some big shot's daughter,
and I heard you're engaged, even,

77
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,160
yet you're here alone with my husband?

78
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,200
How shameless!

79
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:51,400
Calm down, Prao.

80
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:56,720
If you maintained your relationship,
no one could take him from you.

81
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:59,240
Well, does your fiancé know about this?

82
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:02,800
Or perhaps

83
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,920
he's also a homewrecker like you!

84
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:11,720
Enough, Prao. Stop disrespecting others.

85
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,360
We have to talk.

86
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:16,320
Pat! What the hell? Let go!

87
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,680
- Let go of me, Pat.
- Prao.

88
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:27,520
You've misunderstood me, Prao.

89
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,840
Can you listen to me for a change?

90
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:32,360
You two were alone together,
yet you're saying I misunderstood you?

91
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:35,679
Bell asked to rent the house
and use it as her studio.

92
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:38,880
I figured it's vacant anyway,
so I let her rent it.

93
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,840
It's not what you think.

94
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:43,600
Before, when people wanted to rent it,
you didn't allow it.

95
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,720
So how come you let her?

96
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:49,680
Because she values this house, Prao,

97
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,840
whereas you never cared about it.

98
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:55,280
You didn't even bother to come here.

99
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:06,040
I'm using the house
as my dad's temporary office,

100
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,920
so please tell her to move out!

101
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:12,400
This house is mine,
so it's my call what I do with it.

102
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,120
Are you that crazy over her, Pat?!

103
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:25,560
Fine.

104
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:30,520
You can let her rent the house
if you want.

105
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,960
But on one condition.

106
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:57,880
Hey.

107
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,840
Are you okay?

108
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:05,480
I apologize on her behalf.

109
00:10:07,120 --> 00:10:08,240
I'm okay.

110
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:10,440
I understand how your wife feels.

111
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:13,520
She saw you with me, so she got jealous

112
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,280
and couldn't control her emotions.

113
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:18,800
It's not your fault at all, though.

114
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:22,720
Prao and I have had issues
for a very long time.

115
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:27,600
Clarity can make everything better,

116
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:32,200
but it can only be better
if you know what your heart wants.

117
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:40,000
Please give me some more time.

118
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:46,920
How are you going to handle this?

119
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:54,600
<i>Fine. You can let her</i>
<i>rent the house if you want.</i>

120
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,520
But on one condition.

121
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,360
You have to join my dad's party
and run for office.

122
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:08,440
Hey, I'm good with whatever you decide.

123
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:12,920
I'll leave if I'm making
you uncomfortable.

124
00:11:19,480 --> 00:11:21,520
You aren't making me uncomfortable.

125
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:25,960
You just helped me with my decision.

126
00:11:50,040 --> 00:11:50,880
Okay.

127
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:54,760
Whan, the pictures Mr. Thee chose
are in here.

128
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:57,280
Edit them and run
the artworks by me first.

129
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:58,680
- Okay.
- Okay.

130
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:13,400
It's just…

131
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:16,320
I was just reviewing
the photos we had from before,

132
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,520
in case there's any that we can use.

133
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:32,320
Whan, can you zoom in
on that kid on the board?

134
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:35,040
- Try zooming in.
- Okay.

135
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:44,680
Done.

136
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:03,800
Whan, can you send me this photo?

137
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:06,840
Mook.

138
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,440
Uh, Mook?

139
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:14,480
May, where is she rushing off to?

140
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:16,440
Who knows? I'm right here with you.

141
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,120
We should let her be for now.

142
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,760
She probably still can't move on.

143
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:37,880
PIAMSUK ORPHANAGE

144
00:13:57,280 --> 00:14:02,680
PIAMSUK ORPHANAGE

145
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:18,440
Hello. Can I help you with anything?

146
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:22,040
- Hello, Teacher.
- Hello.

147
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:24,840
I've been here before. Do you remember me?

148
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,720
Oh, Ms. Mook.
You were with Mr. Thee, right?

149
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:32,360
Yes. I wanted to ask you about something.

150
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:42,200
I was wondering, what's the name
of the boy in the photo,

151
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:44,560
and where is he now?

152
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:53,600
I just so happened to find a photo
of a kid who looked similar,

153
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:56,080
so I wanted to find out
if it's the same kid.

154
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:59,320
And where did you find that photo?

155
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,120
At the house of an acquaintance.

156
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,040
Her name's Narin.

157
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,760
- Could you tell me about his background--
- Sorry, Ms. Mook.

158
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:09,320
I'm very sorry.

159
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:11,760
We have a rule against
disclosing information

160
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:13,600
of the children here to outsiders.

161
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:19,360
Then, can I at least know his name?

162
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:22,040
It's Ake. His name is Ake.

163
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:27,120
Thank you.

164
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:30,560
I've taken up enough of your time,
so if you'll excuse me.

165
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:33,320
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

166
00:15:57,480 --> 00:16:00,000
Thank you for always
remembering this place, Saifah.

167
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:05,960
And I couldn't be happier to see
that you're living such a great life.

168
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:11,280
If it weren't for you,
I wouldn't be where I am now.

169
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:16,160
I'm happy to do anything
to make those children happy.

170
00:16:21,640 --> 00:16:22,840
Teacher,

171
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:25,600
could you do me a favor?

172
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:32,000
If anyone asks about me,

173
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:35,040
can you cover for me?

174
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:40,080
Even if you didn't ask,
I would do it anyway.

175
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:44,880
Mrs. Anna told me right from the start
not to tell anyone about your background.

176
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,600
But I've never forgotten

177
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:51,200
who I am, where I come from,

178
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:55,200
and how certain people have hurt me.

179
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:29,640
PIAMSUK ORPHANAGE

180
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:31,600
Ms. Mook came here yesterday.

181
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:34,720
She brought your childhood photo
and asked me who the kid was.

182
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:40,160
I didn't tell her anything, though.

183
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:42,920
I even lied and said his name was Ake.

184
00:17:50,520 --> 00:17:53,200
FAVORITES
MOOK - MR. PITAK

185
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:07,400
I'll handle it from here.

186
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:09,200
- I really appreciate it, Teacher.
- No problem.

187
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:43,000
Why are you here?

188
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:44,360
We don't have a meeting today.

189
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:46,240
Where are you going?

190
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,600
I'm going to see Ms. Narin.

191
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:53,240
There's more work I'd like you to edit.

192
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:57,080
You could've called me or mailed me.

193
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:59,640
You shouldn't be here
unless it's important.

194
00:19:00,240 --> 00:19:01,720
I don't want any more trouble.

195
00:19:06,040 --> 00:19:08,000
Did you go to Piamsuk Orphanage?

196
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:14,040
How'd you know?

197
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:16,600
I was talking to Ms. Tassanee
about the grant for the kids.

198
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:19,400
She told me you went there yesterday.

199
00:19:19,480 --> 00:19:21,120
What were you doing there?

200
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:25,560
I had something to take care of.

201
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,560
Is it my job to tell you about it?

202
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:32,640
Come on. Let's talk about work.

203
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:35,920
Please let me know
what you'd like me to edit.

204
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:55,920
Mr. Thee.

205
00:19:57,080 --> 00:19:59,160
- Hello.
- Hello, Mr. Pat.

206
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:03,000
- Are you here to see Mook?
- Yes.

207
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:06,920
Do you have a minute?

208
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:10,160
I wanted to talk to you about something.

209
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:24,320
RUAM JAI PARTY - COLLABORATE
AND HELP IMPROVE THE THAI SOCIETY

210
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:42,160
Why isn't Pat here yet?

211
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:45,840
Are you sure
he'll be able to apply in time?

212
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:51,800
Yes, I am. I offered him a deal.

213
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:55,480
You can let her rent the house
if you want.

214
00:20:58,320 --> 00:20:59,840
But on one condition.

215
00:21:00,480 --> 00:21:03,240
You have to join my dad's party
and run for office.

216
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:14,640
Don't think he'll always cave in
just because you have the upper hand.

217
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:19,120
When we men don't want something,
we'll never do it.

218
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:20,280
That much is certain.

219
00:21:23,520 --> 00:21:27,040
But I'm sure Pat's not that kind of guy.

220
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:31,680
Hello, Mr. Pansak.

221
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:35,800
Hello! Please, let's go inside.

222
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:38,600
- Please, go ahead.
- Please, come on in.

223
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:40,480
- Come on in.
- Come on in.

224
00:21:40,560 --> 00:21:42,200
Let's go over the details.

225
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:45,000
FAVORITES - PAT

226
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:20,800
I'm sorry, Ms. Narin. I don't understand
why Mr. Thee did this either.

227
00:22:22,160 --> 00:22:24,760
Mr. Thee got the rest
of our hotel's shares

228
00:22:25,360 --> 00:22:27,680
because you helped him,
didn't you, Mr. Chadchai?

229
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:30,040
I just figured

230
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:33,120
that if a skilled investor like him
helped run our hotel,

231
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:37,600
he could get us out of the red.

232
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:40,000
But I swear I didn't know

233
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:43,560
he'd remove you from the board like this.

234
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:57,560
Come on in.

235
00:23:03,440 --> 00:23:04,640
What's up, Boss?

236
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,480
It sure is hard to find you these days.

237
00:23:11,280 --> 00:23:14,280
I wonder if there's something
you haven't told me.

238
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:19,560
Well, I'm about to tell you now.

239
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:28,120
I've decided, Mook.

240
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:32,360
I'm stepping out of my comfort zone.

241
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:35,600
What do you mean?

242
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:43,360
I'm divorcing Prao.

243
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,760
What made you come to that decision?

244
00:23:51,560 --> 00:23:53,680
Bell helped me see new perspectives

245
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:57,440
and gave me the courage
to face my problems.

246
00:24:00,320 --> 00:24:01,680
And I think

247
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:05,600
I'm not the only one who thinks that.

248
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:38,440
Who on earth did this?

249
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:41,120
Prao.

250
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:54,080
Do you like the way
I decorated the studio?

251
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:55,800
Why'd you do this, Prao?

252
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:59,200
Well, you didn't come like you promised.

253
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:00,840
You humiliated me in front of my dad.

254
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:02,400
That's what you deserve.

255
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:23,760
I'm sorry.

256
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,280
This doesn't bother me at all.

257
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:35,600
This is nothing
compared to what I'm used to.

258
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:50,840
Okay, I'll take care of it
for you right away.

259
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:52,160
Yes, thank you.

260
00:25:55,160 --> 00:25:57,480
- Oh, Ms. Mook!
- Good morning, Ms. Narin.

261
00:25:57,560 --> 00:25:59,360
Good morning. You're here so early.

262
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:00,520
Do you need something?

263
00:26:01,400 --> 00:26:05,120
I heard that Mr. Thee's
removing you from the board.

264
00:26:07,160 --> 00:26:10,320
Yes, Mr. Chadchai informed me.

265
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:13,320
Mr. Thee will probably
make it official soon.

266
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:16,680
Have you met him before?

267
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:20,160
I don't think so.

268
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:24,560
If you've never met him
or had a conflict with his business,

269
00:26:25,160 --> 00:26:27,560
then why did he do this to you?

270
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:30,960
To be honest,

271
00:26:31,600 --> 00:26:35,240
I don't quite understand
why he did it either.

272
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:39,800
But whenever he sees you,

273
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:42,280
I feel like he…

274
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:44,600
Doesn't seem to like me, right?

275
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:46,560
Yes.

276
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:49,480
I felt it too.

277
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:52,440
And I feel like I've met him before.

278
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:54,440
It's strange.

279
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:57,160
I thought long and hard,
but I couldn't figure it out.

280
00:27:04,840 --> 00:27:08,920
Ms. Narin, I wanted to ask you
about something.

281
00:27:19,680 --> 00:27:22,080
These two boys are my sons.

282
00:27:28,360 --> 00:27:29,280
There was an incident,

283
00:27:30,760 --> 00:27:34,160
and since then, I haven't seen them.

284
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:40,920
Would you mind telling me what happened?

285
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:47,080
My two sons and I

286
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:50,080
lived in a slum.

287
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:55,120
Even though we were very poor
and had to skip many meals,

288
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:58,960
we were quite happy.

289
00:28:01,080 --> 00:28:04,160
That is, until the incident happened
that changed my life forever.

290
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,360
<i>That day,</i>

291
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:11,320
<i>I was out doing some odd jobs.</i>

292
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:16,440
<i>And after work,</i>
<i>I bought dinner for my kids,</i>

293
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:19,400
<i>just like I did every day before.</i>

294
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:25,200
Little did I know that after that,

295
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:28,720
I'd never get to see my kids again.

296
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:01,520
Ma'am?

297
00:29:03,760 --> 00:29:04,840
Ma'am?

298
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:07,200
Her blood pressure's normal,

299
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:10,080
and so is her heart rate.

300
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:12,600
She's stable now,

301
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:19,000
but she had a severe concussion
that may cause dementia,

302
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:21,880
which has to do with memory loss.

303
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:24,000
It might cause temporary memory loss.

304
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:27,200
We might need to do another MRI.

305
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:28,520
But in most cases,

306
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:33,600
we can get the patient to fully recover,
so please don't worry.

307
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:03,560
Try looking straight ahead, please.

308
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:11,920
Does your head hurt?

309
00:30:12,760 --> 00:30:14,040
No, it doesn't.

310
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:17,280
- What's your name?
- My name is Narin.

311
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:19,360
Do you remember anything?

312
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:23,560
For example, where do you live?

313
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:25,080
How many siblings do you have?

314
00:30:34,640 --> 00:30:35,440
It's alright.

315
00:30:35,520 --> 00:30:38,840
Your memory will gradually recover.

316
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:40,560
In about two weeks,

317
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:43,600
we'll be able to start
your physical therapy.

318
00:30:44,200 --> 00:30:45,360
Thank you.

319
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:01,480
Please get plenty of rest.

320
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:09,400
Now, move the leg that hurts.

321
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:12,000
Good. Do your legs hurt?

322
00:31:12,080 --> 00:31:13,480
Easy, okay?

323
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:16,880
Now step.

324
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,600
Okay.

325
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:39,320
How are my kids?

326
00:32:41,520 --> 00:32:43,080
Has anyone seen them?

327
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:47,760
I found out a while ago

328
00:32:48,360 --> 00:32:50,440
that you used to live here
with your children.

329
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:53,160
When I first got here,

330
00:32:53,680 --> 00:32:56,000
your house was already in this state.

331
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:00,200
Whoa there.

332
00:34:00,280 --> 00:34:03,720
Tawan, don't fight.
Share with your brother, okay?

333
00:34:03,800 --> 00:34:05,080
- Okay.
- Okay.

334
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:07,040
- Here.
- Okay.

335
00:34:07,120 --> 00:34:09,120
- Here. Try again.
- Yeah, just like that.

336
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:11,480
- Whoa.
- Here.

337
00:34:31,560 --> 00:34:33,080
Please calm down, ma'am.

338
00:34:33,600 --> 00:34:35,199
I'll have people help find them.

339
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:39,600
I'll go to the police,
so they can help find them too,

340
00:34:40,159 --> 00:34:42,159
in case someone knows where they are.

341
00:34:44,639 --> 00:34:46,199
No…

342
00:34:48,199 --> 00:34:52,400
My kids!

343
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:03,040
Once I recovered,

344
00:35:04,120 --> 00:35:06,960
I tried to find them for many years,

345
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:10,720
but I never heard from them again.

346
00:35:12,200 --> 00:35:15,320
I don't even know if they're still alive.

347
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:18,200
To this day,

348
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:23,040
it's still something
I can't get out of my mind.

349
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:32,280
What about the person who ran you over?

350
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:35,200
Mr. Songyod.

351
00:35:35,280 --> 00:35:37,640
He paid all the expenses

352
00:35:37,720 --> 00:35:40,200
and took great care of me
after my recovery.

353
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:42,800
Ever since I recovered,

354
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:47,160
we've always stayed in touch
and took care of each other.

355
00:35:48,320 --> 00:35:50,280
Eventually, he asked me to marry him,

356
00:35:51,480 --> 00:35:53,800
and he also had this hotel built.

357
00:35:55,480 --> 00:35:57,080
But unfortunately,

358
00:35:58,200 --> 00:36:00,080
soon after the hotel was finished,

359
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:02,880
he passed away in an accident.

360
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:08,960
So you've been running the hotel
for Mr. Songyod?

361
00:36:10,480 --> 00:36:11,440
Yes.

362
00:36:13,120 --> 00:36:14,640
But even after that,

363
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:18,400
I never stopped searching for my kids.

364
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:25,080
I've always had hope

365
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:30,720
that one day I'll meet them before I die.

366
00:36:32,880 --> 00:36:35,040
If you get to see them again,

367
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:37,840
will you remember them?

368
00:36:40,880 --> 00:36:42,720
It's been so many years.

369
00:36:44,080 --> 00:36:46,360
They must be all grown up now.

370
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:48,720
I might not remember them.

371
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:06,000
Ms. Narin, please take a look
at this photo. Here.

372
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:11,200
Saifah!

373
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:13,160
Saifah.

374
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:15,320
It's Saifah. He's my son.

375
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:17,800
Yes, definitely! It really is him!

376
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:19,360
Saifah?

377
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:21,680
Yes, he's Saifah, my eldest son.

378
00:37:21,760 --> 00:37:23,480
Where'd you find this photo?

379
00:37:23,560 --> 00:37:25,120
Please take me there!

380
00:37:25,640 --> 00:37:27,720
- Ms. Narin. Please calm down.
- Ms. Mook.

381
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:30,560
- Ms. Mook.
- Ms. Narin, what's wrong? Ms. Narin!

382
00:37:30,640 --> 00:37:32,600
Help! Somebody help!

383
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:34,480
Ms. Narin! Ms. Narin!

384
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:36,640
Please hang in there, Ms. Narin.

385
00:37:36,720 --> 00:37:39,280
Somebody help! Ms. Narin!

386
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:43,600
Ms. Narin's in this state
partly because of me.

387
00:37:47,480 --> 00:37:49,640
Please don't blame yourself, Mr. Chadchai.

388
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:54,560
The reason she's in this state
has nothing to do with you.

389
00:37:56,720 --> 00:38:00,160
Well, she got removed from her position
because of me.

390
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:02,080
I was greedy
for the money Mr. Thee offered.

391
00:38:04,600 --> 00:38:08,400
Did Mr. Thee tell you
why he removed her from her position?

392
00:38:09,240 --> 00:38:10,400
No.

393
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:14,040
But I swear I didn't know he'd do this.

394
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:19,000
Ms. Narin is a very caring boss
who takes great care of us.

395
00:38:20,120 --> 00:38:22,440
Our hotel's been
in a severe crisis lately.

396
00:38:22,520 --> 00:38:25,680
I figured if Mr. Thee helped
run the hotel, it'd be good for us,

397
00:38:25,760 --> 00:38:26,920
since he's very skilled.

398
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:32,280
But we didn't want Ms. Narin
to be removed either.

399
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:35,760
Can you talk to Mr. Thee for us?

400
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:12,080
I want to talk to you
about our kids' marriage.

401
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:15,120
That's a good idea.
They've been engaged for a while now.

402
00:39:15,200 --> 00:39:18,240
I think it's about time.

403
00:39:20,040 --> 00:39:23,000
Should we set a date, then?

404
00:39:23,680 --> 00:39:25,720
I want the wedding to happen

405
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,760
before we sign the contract
for the megaproject.

406
00:39:28,640 --> 00:39:31,960
That way, we'll have
an auspicious ceremony to precede it.

407
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:33,960
Sounds good.

408
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:43,280
There won't be a wedding.

409
00:39:46,720 --> 00:39:49,960
Bell and I will not get married.

410
00:39:53,760 --> 00:39:55,520
We don't love each other,

411
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:59,280
and more importantly,
I already love someone else.

412
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:02,320
That divorced single mom?

413
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:04,600
I won't allow it.

414
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:07,920
You have to marry Bell.

415
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:09,320
No,

416
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:13,000
I won't do what I don't want to anymore.

417
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,360
Stop it, Thee.

418
00:40:21,280 --> 00:40:24,320
If you walk out now,
you'll be left with nothing.

419
00:40:36,400 --> 00:40:37,720
I'm sorry, Dad.

420
00:40:44,960 --> 00:40:46,920
When did he find a woman he likes?

421
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:53,800
I'll handle this. Please don't worry.

422
00:40:54,320 --> 00:40:55,640
Everything will go back to normal.

423
00:41:16,880 --> 00:41:17,840
Thee!

424
00:41:22,720 --> 00:41:24,920
Are you sure you want to do this?

425
00:41:25,640 --> 00:41:29,040
It's time we decided our own path, Bell.

426
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:34,160
And I'm sure there's someone
who's ready to take care of you

427
00:41:34,240 --> 00:41:36,240
and make you very happy.

428
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:39,200
What do you mean?

429
00:41:42,880 --> 00:41:44,520
Do you have a minute?

430
00:41:45,120 --> 00:41:47,800
I wanted to talk to you about something.

431
00:42:02,280 --> 00:42:03,640
I love Ms. Bell.

432
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,120
You know,

433
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:11,960
I'm glad to hear it from your mouth.

434
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:17,080
So, you aren't angry with me?

435
00:42:19,400 --> 00:42:22,800
Why would I be angry with someone
who loves someone who's like my sister?

436
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:34,280
Bell is a girl who lacks love and warmth.

437
00:42:35,480 --> 00:42:37,400
I can't give her those things,

438
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:43,160
but still, I've always looked after her
and cared about her.

439
00:42:47,480 --> 00:42:49,480
But you two are engaged.

440
00:42:50,680 --> 00:42:52,720
You'll have to get married anyway, right?

441
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:57,280
I won't do it.

442
00:43:01,840 --> 00:43:03,520
And I'm not worried at all

443
00:43:05,080 --> 00:43:07,160
because Bell will get to meet someone good

444
00:43:08,680 --> 00:43:12,520
who can really love her and protect her.

445
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:26,680
You've known about me
and Mr. Pat all along?

446
00:43:27,720 --> 00:43:30,520
You're my sister. Of course I'd know.

447
00:43:31,040 --> 00:43:32,400
Boss.

448
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:34,200
Bell?

449
00:43:46,360 --> 00:43:48,760
How come you came with Mr. Pat last night?

450
00:43:48,840 --> 00:43:50,840
It's a long story, Thee.

451
00:43:53,480 --> 00:43:56,640
You're done, right?
Want to leave together?

452
00:43:58,400 --> 00:44:00,040
Let's go get changed so we can go.

453
00:44:00,120 --> 00:44:01,480
I'm getting a bit tired.

454
00:44:09,520 --> 00:44:11,360
Mr. Pat's a sweet man.

455
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:16,240
But he's still got a bond.

456
00:44:17,200 --> 00:44:19,680
He needs to handle things properly.

457
00:44:19,760 --> 00:44:24,440
If he still can't do it,
I won't let you get involved with him.

458
00:44:29,800 --> 00:44:34,040
But I can tell
that Mr. Pat's serious about you, Bell.

459
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:40,040
Are you sure your mom
will give in that easily?

460
00:44:41,080 --> 00:44:42,480
I've decided,

461
00:44:43,760 --> 00:44:45,880
and I'm ready to accept the consequences.

462
00:45:05,520 --> 00:45:07,560
Suetrong, about the budget request…

463
00:45:08,640 --> 00:45:09,480
One second.

464
00:45:11,800 --> 00:45:13,120
Is Pat here?

465
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:16,440
Mr. Pat…

466
00:45:19,400 --> 00:45:20,520
Oh no.

467
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:27,320
She just got here,
but I can already feel the steam boiling.

468
00:45:33,600 --> 00:45:35,560
So you're finally in your office?

469
00:45:36,760 --> 00:45:38,720
I thought you'd be somewhere
with her again.

470
00:45:40,200 --> 00:45:43,200
If you're here
to talk nonsense, then leave.

471
00:45:49,000 --> 00:45:50,800
Go see my dad with me, now.

472
00:45:50,880 --> 00:45:53,160
You need to apologize
for standing him up that day.

473
00:45:54,400 --> 00:45:57,080
I never told you I'd go.

474
00:45:58,280 --> 00:45:59,960
How dare you go against me?

475
00:46:05,320 --> 00:46:07,240
I won't do
what you want me to anymore, Prao.

476
00:46:10,560 --> 00:46:15,440
If only I had been more firm,
our love life wouldn't have fallen apart.

477
00:46:20,720 --> 00:46:22,680
Let's get divorced
and get it over with, Prao.

478
00:46:32,960 --> 00:46:34,680
POONPUN'S SCHOOL

479
00:46:39,560 --> 00:46:40,840
Hello?

480
00:46:43,160 --> 00:46:45,120
Got it. I'll be right over.

481
00:46:49,440 --> 00:46:52,120
Pun's teacher said he had a fight
with his friend at school.

482
00:47:05,920 --> 00:47:08,280
I'm glad you're both here.

483
00:47:09,640 --> 00:47:11,080
What happened, Teacher?

484
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:14,560
- Poonpun punched his friend in class.
- No way.

485
00:47:15,560 --> 00:47:18,680
Poonpun's a good kid. He'd never do that.

486
00:47:18,760 --> 00:47:19,680
I'm his mother.

487
00:47:19,760 --> 00:47:21,040
I know what my son is like.

488
00:47:27,440 --> 00:47:29,400
Actually, he wasn't like this before.

489
00:47:30,160 --> 00:47:32,640
He used to be so happy and cheerful.

490
00:47:33,360 --> 00:47:35,960
But lately, he's been keeping to himself.

491
00:47:36,680 --> 00:47:39,280
He's also hot-tempered and violent.

492
00:47:39,360 --> 00:47:41,560
He never does that. I don't believe it.

493
00:47:43,160 --> 00:47:46,520
There are many reasons
for a child's behavioral changes.

494
00:47:47,480 --> 00:47:51,680
For example, his emotions
might be triggered inadvertently.

495
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:54,720
I invited both of you here today

496
00:47:54,800 --> 00:48:00,720
to ask you if there's been
anything unusual at home,

497
00:48:01,320 --> 00:48:03,320
or if there's been an incident

498
00:48:03,920 --> 00:48:07,000
that was traumatic for your son.

499
00:48:08,520 --> 00:48:10,000
What are you trying to say?

500
00:48:11,080 --> 00:48:13,120
A kid's behavior can change

501
00:48:13,200 --> 00:48:15,440
when they've been exposed to violence,

502
00:48:15,520 --> 00:48:18,320
such as raising your voice,

503
00:48:18,920 --> 00:48:21,400
arguing, or fighting,

504
00:48:21,480 --> 00:48:24,760
all of which can lead
to behavioral changes in kids.

505
00:48:28,400 --> 00:48:32,440
Are you accusing us
of making our son troubled?

506
00:48:33,040 --> 00:48:35,600
Prao, let her explain first.

507
00:48:38,960 --> 00:48:40,800
I'm sorry,

508
00:48:40,880 --> 00:48:45,600
but we need to find the cause
that made Poonpun act this way.

509
00:48:46,320 --> 00:48:51,880
I hope you don't mind me asking
about his behavior at home.

510
00:48:51,960 --> 00:48:55,440
Because if he sees his parents
fighting at home,

511
00:48:55,520 --> 00:48:57,800
he'll mimic that,

512
00:48:57,880 --> 00:48:59,600
which leads to aggressive behavior

513
00:48:59,680 --> 00:49:02,440
because he's mimicking what he's seen.

514
00:49:03,160 --> 00:49:05,120
How should we handle him, then?

515
00:49:05,200 --> 00:49:08,800
It helps to stop behaving violently
in front of your kid.

516
00:49:09,760 --> 00:49:12,400
I'm counting on you both.

517
00:49:12,480 --> 00:49:15,880
We'll have to help each other,
both at school and at home.

518
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:21,960
Of course, Teacher.

519
00:50:12,600 --> 00:50:13,800
Good evening.

520
00:50:33,320 --> 00:50:36,280
You really changed Thee, Veluree.

521
00:50:38,760 --> 00:50:40,840
I don't know what you're talking about,

522
00:50:41,440 --> 00:50:43,360
but it's already over
between me and Mr. Thee.

523
00:50:43,440 --> 00:50:46,920
How could it be over
when he's refusing to get married?

524
00:50:47,440 --> 00:50:49,280
He even disobeyed my orders.

525
00:50:52,200 --> 00:50:56,680
He's never been this way before
until he met you.

526
00:51:01,120 --> 00:51:03,160
You want my son so badly, don't you?

527
00:51:05,280 --> 00:51:06,360
Fine.

528
00:51:07,080 --> 00:51:08,440
You can have him.

529
00:51:09,800 --> 00:51:14,960
But you can only take him,
and not TJ Group's assets.

530
00:51:19,920 --> 00:51:22,120
If he chooses a woman like you over me,

531
00:51:22,200 --> 00:51:25,480
who adopted him, then so be it.

532
00:51:28,560 --> 00:51:31,800
But if you're hoping to marry into money,

533
00:51:32,400 --> 00:51:33,920
then dream on.

534
00:52:14,680 --> 00:52:15,960
Whoa, hey!

535
00:52:16,960 --> 00:52:20,320
Easy there, or you'll end up on the floor.

536
00:52:33,520 --> 00:52:35,520
You were born with a silver spoon,

537
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:37,800
so you never had to struggle.

538
00:52:38,920 --> 00:52:41,000
That's why you don't know
money's true value.

539
00:52:42,640 --> 00:52:43,480
How would you know

540
00:52:46,120 --> 00:52:47,560
I've never had to struggle?

541
00:52:50,560 --> 00:52:52,480
Has anyone ever left you before?

542
00:52:54,400 --> 00:52:57,160
You're not mad at me anymore, right?

543
00:52:57,240 --> 00:52:59,480
I was never mad at you.

544
00:53:00,480 --> 00:53:02,440
I was the one who broke my promise.

545
00:53:02,520 --> 00:53:05,840
Uncle Thee told me you love me the most,

546
00:53:05,920 --> 00:53:08,040
and he also told me that

547
00:53:08,120 --> 00:53:13,600
I'm luckier than him to still have my mom.

548
00:53:13,680 --> 00:53:15,840
<i>Unlike me, his mom left him.</i>

549
00:53:22,240 --> 00:53:26,520
<i>Sorry, the number you've dialed</i>
<i>is currently--.</i>

550
00:53:30,680 --> 00:53:33,560
<i>Sorry, the number you've dialed--</i>

551
00:53:58,400 --> 00:54:00,240
NOTICE OF TERMINATION OF CEO
DEAR SHAREHOLDERS AND EXECUTIVES

552
00:54:00,320 --> 00:54:02,080
BEST REGARDS
MR. THEECHUDA TEERASU (CEO)

553
00:54:11,560 --> 00:54:12,760
Ms. Mook!

554
00:54:19,400 --> 00:54:21,000
Are you here to see Mr. Thee?

555
00:54:22,440 --> 00:54:26,000
Is it true what Mrs. Anna said?

556
00:54:28,200 --> 00:54:31,600
Yes. Mrs. Anna
adopted Mr. Thee as her son.

557
00:54:34,400 --> 00:54:38,720
I've warned him before
that this would happen one day.

558
00:54:40,400 --> 00:54:42,440
And it really did.

559
00:54:43,200 --> 00:54:47,040
Mrs. Anna was very angry
that Mr. Thee's refusing to get married.

560
00:54:47,880 --> 00:54:49,680
<i>Are you sure about this, Mr. Thee?</i>

561
00:54:52,280 --> 00:54:54,200
Mrs. Anna seemed very angry.

562
00:55:00,480 --> 00:55:01,640
Yes.

563
00:55:03,360 --> 00:55:04,840
I've thought it through.

564
00:55:04,920 --> 00:55:09,880
But you do know
what will happen after this, right?

565
00:55:10,520 --> 00:55:12,360
I'm ready to accept it.

566
00:55:21,120 --> 00:55:24,880
I've done everything I set out to do.

567
00:55:28,360 --> 00:55:30,800
I'm ready to go back to where I belong,

568
00:55:32,160 --> 00:55:33,280
Mr. Pitak.

569
00:55:37,280 --> 00:55:38,400
Adopted?

570
00:55:39,440 --> 00:55:40,680
From where?

571
00:55:43,240 --> 00:55:44,480
Piamsuk Orphanage.

572
00:56:12,960 --> 00:56:13,800
Mook!

573
00:56:15,680 --> 00:56:16,960
What are you doing here?

574
00:56:24,400 --> 00:56:25,760
Ms. Narin's severely ill.

575
00:56:26,760 --> 00:56:28,800
She's in hospital right now.

576
00:56:35,320 --> 00:56:36,800
Why are you telling me this?

577
00:56:37,560 --> 00:56:39,720
That woman's got nothing to do with me.

578
00:56:41,040 --> 00:56:42,040
Saifah!

579
00:56:47,000 --> 00:56:48,480
Saifah, help me!

580
00:56:48,560 --> 00:56:51,160
- There's a fire! Come on, come here!
- Please help my brother!

581
00:56:51,240 --> 00:56:53,040
No! Let go of me!

582
00:56:53,120 --> 00:56:54,160
Mr. Thee!

583
00:56:54,240 --> 00:56:57,440
Do you have any idea
how much we had to suffer?!

584
00:56:57,520 --> 00:56:59,360
How could you leave your kids?!

585
00:56:59,440 --> 00:57:01,080
- Mr. Thee!
- How could you!

586
00:57:01,160 --> 00:57:03,600
How about Tawan, honey? Did he come too?

587
00:57:03,680 --> 00:57:06,720
Is your brother here too? Is he?

588
00:57:07,320 --> 00:57:08,320
Where is he?

589
00:57:08,400 --> 00:57:10,160
Even though I've met my mom,

590
00:57:12,160 --> 00:57:13,960
I never thought of leaving you.

591
00:57:14,040 --> 00:57:18,120
No! You have no choice
but to be someone I've created,

592
00:57:18,200 --> 00:57:21,920
and I'm the only mother you can have.

593
00:58:16,120 --> 00:58:18,320
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya
